  "messages": [
    {
      "id": 1341,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:33",
      "content": "The operator sees two identical bus messages \"Yes, proceed\" (IDs #1337 and #1338) sent at the same timestamp (2026-06-08T10:27:22). This happened when the operator clicked the \"Approve\" button on an approval request in S-Deck.\n\n**Investigate why the approve action sends the message twice.**\n\nLook at:\n1. The S-Deck frontend — find the Approve button click handler. Is it firing twice (double-submit, missing `preventDefault`, event bubbling, etc.)?\n2. The backend approval endpoint (if any) — is it persisting and broadcasting the reply once or twice?\n3. The bus `send_message` path — could there be a duplicate insertion in the DB?\n\nCheck `src/`, `public/app.js`, and any relevant event handling code. Identify the root cause and fix it.\n\n**Work in a worktree:**\nRun: `synapse worktree create developer-33-fix-duplicate-approval`\nWork in `.synapse/worktrees/developer-33-fix-duplicate-approval`. Commit the fix. Do not push.\n\nReport DONE with root cause and what was changed.",
